-- SHFE Will Add a Night Session for Industrial Metals Trading
-- B y   M a r i a   K o l e s n i k o v a
-- 2013-11-25T18:04:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-11-25/shfe-will-add-a-night-session-for-industrial-metals-trading.html
The  Shanghai  Futures Exchange said
it will extend trading hours for copper, aluminum, zinc and lead
by adding a night session from Dec. 20.  The trading will be held from 9 p.m. to 1 a.m. Shanghai
time the following day, the SHFE said in a statement on its
website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Maria Kolesnikova in London at 
 mkolesnikova@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Whitney McFerron at 
 wmcferron1@bloomberg.net  